sequenceDiagram
    participant CP as Charge Point (OCTT)
    participant CS as Central System (SUT)

    Note over CP,CS: Test Case: TC_087_CSMS
    Note over CP,CS: TLS - Client-side certificate - valid certificate
    Note over CP,CS: Prerequisite: Central System supports security profile 3

    CP->>CS: 1. Initiate TLS handshake (Client Hello)
    CS-->>CP: 2. Server Hello with <Configured server certificate>

    Note over CP: 3. Charge Point performs:<br/>Send client certificate<br/>Client Key Exchange<br/>Certificate verify<br/>Change Cipher Spec<br/>Finished

    Note over CS: 4. Central System performs:<br/>Change Cipher Spec<br/>Finished

    Note over CP,CS: TLS Handshake Complete

    Note right of CP: Tool Validation (Step 3):<br/>- TLS version >= 1.2<br/>- Required cipher suites supported

    CP->>CS: 5. HTTP Upgrade Request

    CS-->>CP: 6. Upgrade to (secured) WebSocket connection

    CP->>CS: 7. BootNotification.req
    CS-->>CP: 8. BootNotification.conf

    CP->>CS: 9. StatusNotification.req (per connector, connectorId=0)
    CS-->>CP: 10. StatusNotification.conf
